    "comment": "Rationale: The authors express HRP-fused recombinant LRRTM2 and observe stainging of the synaptic cleft. LRRTM2 is a postsynaptic TM adhesion protein that is known to be able to induce presynaptic differentiation of GLUTergic synapses. The postsynaptic localization is not resolved in these figures (difficult for epitopes/proteins in/around the synaptic cleft) but known from other literature (seen f.i. ticket #545 that shows expression in the postsynapse). This aspect is implicitly acknowledged by the authors since the study uses HPR-tagging of postsynaptic proteins to separate Glut from GABA synapses (Fig.1A). Experimental description: - \"Dissociated Rat Neuron Culture\"\n- The species of the overexpressed proteins is not stated. The authors were contacted for additional information (dd. 23/2/2018, ayting@stanford.edu). Author replied:\n\n\"the genes are:\nSLITRK3 human\nLRRTM1: human\nLRRTM2: human\nNLGN2A: rat\n\nbest wishes,\n\nKen Loh\nPostdoctoral Associate\nFriedman Lab\n(formerly Ting lab)\"",
